Okechukwu Nnodim, Abuja A total of 19,432 customers under the franchise areas of the Abuja Electricity Distribution Company have been metered through the Meter Asset Provider scheme of the Federal Government. According to the Managing Director, AEDC, Ernest Mupwaya, the customers were metered since the MAP programme started in May. He disclosed this at a retreat for senior officials of the power firm, adding that he was satisfied with the pace at which the MAP project was moving. Mupwaya also noted that about 45,000 customers had applied for meters through the scheme, while 44,000 customers had been verified and permitted to pay. He stated that only 20,000 customers had paid while 19,432 of them had been metered Copyright PUNCH.
